sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant Pi
    participant Extension
    participant MD as Markdown (~/.pi/agent/...)
    participant SQL as SQLite (sessions.db)

    Note over Pi,SQL: ── Session Start ──
    Pi->>Extension: session_start event
    Extension->>MD: load MEMORY.md + USER.md + failures.md
    Extension->>Extension: refresh project skill discovery context
    Extension->>SQL: best-effort Markdown → SQLite sync

    Note over Pi,SQL: ── System Prompt Context ──
    Pi->>Extension: before_agent_start event
    Extension-->>Pi: systemPrompt + memory policy
    Note right of Pi: Default mode does not inject full Markdown memory

    Note over Pi,SQL: ── Agent Loop (memory add) ──
    User->>Pi: "Remember I prefer vim"
    Pi->>Extension: tool_call(memory, add)
    Extension->>Extension: scanContent() security check
    Extension->>MD: atomic write to Markdown
    alt Markdown save success
        Extension->>SQL: best-effort sync to memories table
        Extension-->>Pi: success (warning only if sync fails)
    else Markdown save fails
        Extension-->>Pi: fail (no SQLite-only fallback)
    end

    Note over Pi,SQL: ── User Correction ──
    User->>Pi: "No, don't use npm — use pnpm"
    Extension->>Extension: isCorrection() = true
    Extension->>Pi: pi.exec("pi -p", correction prompt)
    Extension->>MD: save categorized correction/failure memory
    Extension->>SQL: best-effort SQLite sync

    Note over Pi,SQL: ── Search + Backfill ──
    Pi->>Extension: memory_search(query, filters)
    Extension->>SQL: FTS5 search memories
    SQL-->>Extension: fenced stored-memory results
    Pi->>Extension: session_search(query)
    Extension->>SQL: FTS5 search indexed sessions
    SQL-->>Extension: fenced historical results

    Note over Pi,SQL: ── Background Learning ──
    Pi->>Extension: turn_end (10 turns or 15 tool calls)
    Extension->>Pi: pi.exec("pi -p", review prompt)
    Note right of Pi: Review saves memories/failures only; skills are explicit

    Note over Pi,SQL: ── Session End ──
    Pi->>Extension: session_shutdown event
    Extension->>Pi: pi.exec("pi -p", flush prompt)
    Extension->>SQL: index current session file
